   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_269586_1826_05_16_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1826-05-16">May 16<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1826</date>
                  <lb/>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StaeA2">M de Stael</persName> and the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrogA1">Duc de<lb/>
                  Broglie</persName> are honorable men<lb/>
               - no doubt - and doubtless<lb/>
               honorable men will <choice>
                  <orig>remem<lb/>
                  -ber</orig>
                  <reg>remember</reg>
               </choice> and will keep their<lb/>
               promises -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>They promised that when<lb/>
               they revisited my <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#ENK">England</placeName> they<lb/>
               would pay us a visit at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth's Town</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>And now honorable<lb/>
               Gentlemen I trust your<lb/>
               Honors will be as good as<lb/>
               your word--<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>And kind friends I have<lb/>
               so much reliance upon your<lb/>
               kindness that I release you<lb/>
               from your engagement, <choice>
                  <orig>be-<lb/>
                     <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_269586_1826_05_16_page02.jpg"/>
                  cause</orig>
                  <reg>because</reg>
               </choice> I would rather owe<lb/>
               the pleasure of seeing you<lb/>
               entirely to your own <choice>
                  <orig>free-<lb/>
               will</orig>
                  <reg>freewill</reg>
               </choice> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>You ought for your own<lb/>
               sakes, to have the amusement<lb/>
               of seeing the humors of an<lb/>
               election in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> as well<lb/>
               as in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#ENK">England</placeName> - you who have<lb/>
               described an English <add>County</add> meeting<lb/>
               so well must do justice to<lb/>
               an Irish election-- Believe<lb/>
               me it will be rich in traits<lb/>
               of individual &amp; national<lb/>
               character &amp; will give you &amp;<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrogA1">M de Broglie </persName> material for <del>
                  <unclear/>
               </del>
               <lb/>
               months thought<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Edgeworth</persName> my brothers<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_269586_1826_05_16_page03.jpg"/>

               and all this family - <orig>especia<unclear/>
                  <note>watermark</note>
               </orig>
               <reg>especially</reg>
               <lb/>
               those who had the <orig>happi<unclear/>
                  <note>watermark</note>
               </orig>
               <reg>happiness</reg>
               <lb/>
               of being so kindly recieved<lb/>
               by you at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Coppet_SZ">Coppet</placeName> join their<lb/>
               intreaties with mine<lb/>
               that you will give us the<lb/>
               opportunity of returning<lb/>
               some of your hospitality<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Remember too that<lb/>
               you and I have many tangled<lb/>
               subjects of conversation to<lb/>
               wind up -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I hear from all my <add>Parisian</add> friends<lb/>
               on whose judgement I most<lb/>
               depend of the excellence &amp;<lb/>
               the effect of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrogA1">M de
                  Broglie's </persName>
               <lb/>
               discourses - I wish I could<lb/>
               see them - next best to hearing<lb/>
               them<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName> -<lb/>
            </closer>
            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_269586_1826_05_16_page04.jpg"/>
            <postscript>
               <p>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SpriT1">Spring Rice</persName> will convey<lb/>
               to me your answer -<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>a</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Monsieur</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StaeA2">M. le. Baron de Stael</persName>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
